A student of the Makerere University in Kampala, Uganda, Emmanuel Wamono, has drowned in a swimming pool while trying to save a child. According to Ugandan news outlet, Campus Bee, on Sunday, Wamono died at the swimming pool at Mountain Inn Hotel in Mbale. Wamono was a third year electrical engineering student. ALSO READ: Trevor Noah ‘mocks’ Prince Harry over ‘frost-bitten’ private part revelation The news of Wamono’s death was announced in a statement by the Makerere University Dean of Students, Winifred Kabumbuli, on Sunday. The deceased will be buried on Monday at his village in Bunambutye village, Mbale District in Uganda. 